# Queue Rules

## Stack

- Queue: BullMQ (via `@nestjs/bullmq`)
- Broker: Redis

---

## When to Use Queues

Use queues for any work that should not block the HTTP response:
- Sending emails / SMS / push notifications
- Processing file uploads or image resizing
- Webhooks and third-party API calls
- PDF generation / report generation
- Syncing data to external services
- Any operation that takes > 500ms

---

## Setup

```ts
// app.module.ts
BullModule.forRootAsync({
  imports: [ConfigModule],
  useFactory: (config: ConfigService) => ({
    connection: {
      host: config.get('REDIS_HOST'),
      port: config.get('REDIS_PORT'),
    },
  }),
  inject: [ConfigService],
}),

BullModule.registerQueue({ name: 'email' }),
BullModule.registerQueue({ name: 'notification' }),
```

