## Queue Names (Constants)

```ts
// src/common/constants/queues.ts
export const QUEUES = {
  EMAIL: 'email',
  NOTIFICATION: 'notification',
  FILE_PROCESSING: 'file-processing',
  REPORT: 'report',
} as const;
```

---

## Job Names (Constants)

```ts
// src/common/constants/jobs.ts
export const JOBS = {
  SEND_WELCOME_EMAIL: 'send-welcome-email',
  SEND_ORDER_CONFIRMATION: 'send-order-confirmation',
  SEND_PUSH_NOTIFICATION: 'send-push-notification',
  RESIZE_IMAGE: 'resize-image',
  GENERATE_INVOICE: 'generate-invoice',
} as const;
```

---

## Producer (Service)

Add jobs from services, never from controllers:

```ts
@Injectable()
export class NotificationService {
  constructor(
    @InjectQueue(QUEUES.NOTIFICATION)
    private readonly notificationQueue: Queue,
  ) {}

  async sendWelcomeEmail(userId: string, email: string) {
    await this.notificationQueue.add(
      JOBS.SEND_WELCOME_EMAIL,
      { userId, email },
      {
        attempts: 3,
        backoff: { type: 'exponential', delay: 2000 },
        removeOnComplete: 100,
        removeOnFail: 500,
      },
    );
  }
}
```

---

## Consumer (Processor)

```ts
@Processor(QUEUES.NOTIFICATION)
export class NotificationProcessor {
  private readonly logger = new Logger(NotificationProcessor.name);

  constructor(private readonly emailService: EmailService) {}

  @Process(JOBS.SEND_WELCOME_EMAIL)
  async handleWelcomeEmail(job: Job<{ userId: string; email: string }>) {
    this.logger.log(`Processing welcome email for: ${job.data.email}`);

    try {
      await this.emailService.sendWelcome(job.data.email);
      this.logger.log(`Welcome email sent: ${job.data.email}`);
    } catch (error) {
      this.logger.error(`Failed to send welcome email: ${error.message}`, error.stack);
      throw error; // re-throw so BullMQ retries
    }
  }
}
```

---

## Job Options

```ts
{
  attempts: 3,                            // retry 3 times on failure
  backoff: { type: 'exponential', delay: 2000 }, // 2s, 4s, 8s
  removeOnComplete: 100,                  // keep last 100 completed jobs
  removeOnFail: 500,                      // keep last 500 failed jobs
  delay: 5000,                            // delay before processing (ms)
  priority: 1,                            // lower = higher priority
}
```

---

## Rules

- Always use named constants for queue names and job names
- Producers live in services — never add jobs from controllers
- Consumers re-throw errors so BullMQ can retry
- Always set `attempts` and `backoff` — never fire-and-forget without retry
- Log job start, success, and failure in the processor
- Never await a queue job in an HTTP handler — the point is non-blocking
- Use `removeOnComplete` and `removeOnFail` to avoid memory leak in Redis

---

## Forbidden

❌ Adding jobs from controllers
❌ Jobs without retry configuration
❌ Awaiting queue jobs in HTTP handlers
❌ Hardcoded queue/job name strings
❌ Missing error logging in processors
❌ Missing `removeOnComplete` / `removeOnFail` — Redis will grow unbounded
